records.addlTxt:
Defendant Justin A Arguelles in court with attorney Craig Mastantuono.   District Attorney's Office Law Intern appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Defendant pleads guilty to Counts 1 and 5.  Counts 2, 3, 4, 6, 7, 8, 9, 10 and 11 are dismissed and read-in.  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE AS TO COUNT 1 of: 

5 YEARS IMPRISONMENT
  -  2 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;
  -  5 YEAR(S) OF PROBATION;


IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE AS TO COUNT 5 OF:

3 YEARS IMPRISONMENT TO RUN CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1
 - 1 YEAR OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT;
 - 2 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;
 - 3 YEAR(S) OF PROBATION IS CONCURRENT TO COUNT 1;

IF REVOKED, SENTENCES TO RUN CONSECUTIVE WITH EACH OTHER

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Any valid prescription drugs must be taken only in the manner in which they are prescribed.
*Inform Agent of all prescriptions
*Any prescriptions are to be prescribed through the same pharmacy;
*Notify doctors of this case;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full-time employment and/or combination of schooling ;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association/contact with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.

BUY MONEY: $220.00 to the Waukesha County Metro Drug Unit (to be paid as a condition of probation);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 as to each count (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 as to each count (to be paid as a condition of extended supervision);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.

CONDITION TIME:  

Count 1:  8 month jail - straight time (1 day credit).

Count 5: 4 months Huber consecutive to Count 1.  Release for school and/or work.
